   <concept id="FAR_18_201" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">18.201</ph> Contingency operation.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1116e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1144e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Contingency operation is defined
in <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1144e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Micro-purchase
threshold. The threshold increases when the head of the agency determines
the supplies or services are to be used to support a contingency
operation. (See <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> and <xref href="13.201.dita#FAR_13_201"
                        base="i1111870"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.201</xref>(g).)</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1144e29">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Simplified
acquisition threshold. The threshold increases when the head of
the agency determines the supplies or services are to be used to
support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.)</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1144e37">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "/>
                  <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 44</xref>, Purchase
Order-Invoice-Voucher. The normal threshold for the use of the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">SF 44</xref> is
at or below the micro-purchase threshold. Agencies may, however,
establish higher dollar limitations for purchases made to support
a contingency operation. (See <xref href="13.306.dita#FAR_13_306"
                        base="i1111753"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.306</xref>.)</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1144e51">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Simplified
procedures for certain commercial
products and commercial services.
                  </i> The threshold limits
authorized for use of this authority may be increased for acquisitions
to support a contingency operation. (See <xref href="13.500.dita#FAR_13_500"
                        base="i1111260"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.500</xref>(c).)</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
